    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1967-02-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1967-02-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="199"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                <head>199. Memorandum for the Record<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d199fn1"
                        >Source: Central Intelligence Agency: Job 80–B01285A, <gloss
                            target="#t_DCI1">DCI</gloss> (<persName corresp="#p_HRM1"
                            >Helms</persName>) Files, <gloss target="#t_DCI1">DCI</gloss> (<persName
                            corresp="#p_HRM1">Helms</persName>) Memo for the Record, Folder 9.
                        Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1967-02-09">February 9, 1967</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Senate Contacts on United States-Soviet Consular Treaty</item>
                </list>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>After speaking with the President on the telephone, I called Senator
                            <persName corresp="#p_RRB1">Russell</persName> at 11:40 A.M., on 7
                        February, and spoke with him along the lines that the President had
                            suggested.<note n="2" xml:id="d199fn2">Attached is a transcript of
                                <persName corresp="#p_HRM1">Helms</persName>’ February 7
                            conversation with the President.</note> After informing him that I <pb
                            facs="0485" n="457" xml:id="pg_457"/> was seeing Senator <persName
                            corresp="#p_DEM1">Dirksen</persName> that afternoon, I volunteered that
                        since meeting with Senator <persName corresp="#p_RRB1">Russell</persName> on
                        28 January, I had ascertained that the United States Intelligence Board, the
                        Joint Chiefs of Staff, and the Secretary of Defense were all in favor of
                        seeing the Consular Treaty ratified. Senator <persName corresp="#p_RRB1"
                            >Russell</persName> expressed appreciation for this information. He did
                        not ask to talk with me further on this matter.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>At 4:00 P.M., on 7 February, I met with Senator <persName
                            corresp="#p_DEM1">Dirksen</persName>, at his request, in his back office
                        in the Capitol. We spent twenty minutes together. I covered in detail with
                        him the points which the President had suggested, including the support of
                            <gloss target="#t_USIB1">USIB</gloss>, the <gloss target="#t_JCS1"
                            >JCS</gloss>, the Secretary of Defense, and the President’s Foreign
                        Intelligence Advisory Board. [<hi rend="italic">12 lines of source text not
                            declassified</hi>]<note n="3" xml:id="d199fn3">[<hi rend="italic">text
                                not declassified</hi>] which is attached, [<hi rend="italic">text
                                not declassified</hi>]. A copy is also in the Johnson Library,
                            National Security File, Memos to the President—<persName
                                corresp="#p_RWW1">Walt W. Rostow</persName>, Vol. 19, #1a.</note>
                        <note n="4" xml:id="d199fn4">[<hi rend="italic">text not declassified</hi>]
                            which is attached, [<hi rend="italic">text not
                            declassified</hi>].</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Attached are the papers relating to the meeting with Senator <persName
                            corresp="#p_DEM1">Dirksen</persName>.<note n="5" xml:id="d199fn5">Also
                            attached are a transcript of <persName corresp="#p_HRM1"
                                >Helms</persName>’ February 7 telephone conversation with <persName
                                corresp="#p_KNB1">Katzenbach</persName> and a membership list for
                            the President’s Foreign Intelligence Advisory Board.</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">RH</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Director</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
